Doesn't fallback to custom MIME type icon

note.body:
Got it resolved by specifying `generic-icon` instead of `icon` in the shared-mime-info file, apparently generic-icon takes precedence and falls back to `application-x-generic` if not specified. And since Adwaita has an `application-x-generic` icon and Hicolor doesn't, that's what gets chosen.

Now passing a _specific_ icon as generic-icon is probably bad practice and generic icons might provide better UX, but at least I now understand what's happening :)

note.body:
Can we also add other dnd names?
Chromium lists the following cursors:

dnd-none - Usually equivalent to **dnd-move**

dnd-move - Already implemented

dnd-copy - Usually equivalent to **copy**

dnd-link - Merge request

There is also **dnd-ask**, which is used by [GTK itself](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/-/blob/main/gdk/gdkdrag.c#L783) with no CSS fallback, though past Adwaita iterations and other cursor themes usually represent it in a similar fashion to **help**.
